<div class='talk-speakers'>
<div class='talk-speaker media'>
<a class='talk-speaker__image media__image media__image--thumb' href='/speakers/jane_mcgonigal'>
<span class="thumb thumb--square"><span class="thumb__sizer"><span class="thumb__tugger"><img alt="" class=" thumb__image" play="false" src="https://tedcdnpi-a.akamaihd.net/r/tedcdnpe-a.akamaihd.net/images/ted/157052_254x191.jpg?" /><span class="thumb__aligner"></span></span></span></span>
</a>
<div class='talk-speaker__details media__message'>
<div class='talk-speaker__name h10'>
<a class="l3 talk-speaker__link" href="/speakers/jane_mcgonigal">Jane McGonigal</a>
</div>
<div class='talk-speaker__description'>
Game Designer
</div>
<div class='talk-speaker__bio'>
Reality is broken, says Jane McGonigal, and we need to make it work more like a game. Her work shows us how.
<a class="l3 talk-speaker__link" href="/speakers/jane_mcgonigal">Full bio</a>
</div>
